"replacing &susefirewall; with &firewalld;, required changes in &ay;. If you "
"want to reuse existing &productname; <phrase os=\"sles;sled\">12</phrase> "
"<phrase os=\"osuse\">42.3</phrase> a profiles with &productname; 15, you "
"need to adjust them as documented here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Product Selection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &productname; 15, all products are distributed using a single "
"installation medium. Therefore you need to choose which product to install "
"by using the <tag class=\"element\">product</tag> tag. In the following "
"example &sled; is the chosen product:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[<software>\n"
"  <products config:type=\"list\">\n"
"    <product>SLED</product>\n"
"  </products>\n"
"</software>]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In special cases, the medium may contain only one product. If so there is no "
"need to explicitly select a product as described above. &ay; will select the "
"only available product automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For backward compatibility with profiles created for pre- <phrase os=\"sles;"
"sled\">&slea;</phrase> <phrase os=\"osuse\">Leap</phrase> 15 products, &ay; "
"implements a heuristic that selects products automatically. This heuristic "
"will be used when the profile does not contain a <tag class=\"element"
"\">product</tag> element. This heuristic is based on the package and pattern "
"selection in the profile. However, whenever possible, avoid using this "
"mechanism and adapt old profiles to use explicit product selection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the product selection fails, an error is shown and the installation will "
"not be continued."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &productname; 15 installation medium only contains a very minimal set of "
"packages to install. This minimal set only provides an installation "
"environment and does not include any server applications or advanced tools. "
"Additional software repositories, providing more packages are offered as "
"<quote>modules</quote> or <quote>extensions</quote> . They are provided via "
"two alternatives:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "via a registration server (the &scc; or a local SMT/&rmt; proxy)"
