#. Tag: title
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The partitioning back-end previously used by &yast;, <systemitem class="
"\"library\">libstorage</systemitem> , has been replaced by <systemitem class="
"\"library\">libstorage-ng</systemitem> which is designed to allow new "
"capabilities that were not possible before. Despite the back-end change, the "
"XML syntax for profiles has <emphasis>not</emphasis> changed. However, "
"&productname; 15 comes with some general changes, which are explained below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:372
#, no-c-format
msgid "GPT Becomes the Default Partition Type on &x86-64;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &x86-64; systems, GPT is now the preferred partition type. However, if "
"you would like to retain the old behavior, you can explicitly indicate this "
"in the profile by setting the <tag class=\"element\">disklabel</tag> element "
"to <literal>msdos</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:382
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Partition Numbers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&ay; will no longer support forcing partition numbers, as it might not work "
"in some situations. Moreover, GPT is now the preferred partition table type, "
"so partition numbers are less relevant."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, the <tag class=\"element\">partition_nr</tag> tag is still "
"available in order to specify a partition to be reused. Refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"ay.partition_configuration\"/> for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Forcing Primary Partitions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_12_migrate_15.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is still possible to force a partition as <literal>primary</literal> "
"(only on MS-DOS partition tables) by setting the <tag class=\"element"
"\">primary_type</tag> to <literal>primary</literal> . However, any other "
"value, like <literal>logical</literal> , will be ignored by &ay;, which will "
"automatically determine the partition type."
msgstr ""

